# public-surface-forbidden.regex (model-connector consumer override)
#
# Consumer-scoped copy of the Datarim Public Surface Hygiene contract. The
# reusable workflow (Arcanada-one/datarim/.github/workflows/public-surface-lint.yml)
# loads this file via its `regex_file` input instead of the framework default.
#
# Why an override exists (CONN-0228):
#   The framework milestone pattern `\b(M|Phase) ?[1-9][0-9]*\b` false-positives
#   on the public, correct model name `BGE-M3` (the `M3` token of BAAI General
#   Embedding M3). `BGE-M3` is a legitimate external identifier, not a leaked
#   internal milestone code, so scrubbing it from the docs would degrade them.
#   The milestone pattern here is tightened to not match `M<digit>` when it is
#   preceded by a hyphen or alphanumeric (i.e. part of a hyphenated identifier
#   such as `BGE-M3`), while still catching real milestone leaks (`Phase 2`,
#   `M1`, `level M3`). See dev-tools/public-surface-forbidden.regex.spec.bats.
#
# Keep every other pattern byte-identical to the framework default so the only
# behavioural difference is the tightened milestone boundary. When the framework
# pattern is itself fixed upstream, this override can be removed and the workflow
# reverted to the default regex.
#
# Format: one extended-regex pattern per non-empty, non-comment line.

# Internal SDLC artefact references (PRD / creative / plans / insights /
# reflection). Identical to framework default.
\bPRD-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\bcreative-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\bplans-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\binsights-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\breflection-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b

# Internal-only repo paths inside the canonical Datarim layout. Identical to
# framework default.
\bdatarim/(tasks|creative|plans|insights|reflection)/

# Milestone-code references that leak phase / iteration internals. TIGHTENED
# vs framework default: the leading `(^|[^-A-Za-z0-9])` boundary prevents a
# match inside hyphenated identifiers like `BGE-M3` while still flagging
# standalone milestone codes (`M1`, `Phase 2`, `level M3`).
(^|[^-A-Za-z0-9])(M|Phase) ?[1-9][0-9]*\b
